{
  "page": "Vermax",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Velaryon\" title=\"House Velaryon\"><img alt=\"House Velaryon.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/5f/House_Velaryon.svg/50px-House_Velaryon.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/5f/House_Velaryon.svg/75px-House_Velaryon.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/5f/House_Velaryon.svg/100px-House_Velaryon.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\">Vermax</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/50px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/75px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/100px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Prince_Jacaerys_Velaryon_and_his_dragon_Vermax_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Prince Jacaerys Velaryon and his dragon Vermax by Jota Saraiva.jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/91/Prince_Jacaerys_Velaryon_and_his_dragon_Vermax_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg/350px-Prince_Jacaerys_Velaryon_and_his_dragon_Vermax_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"246\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/91/Prince_Jacaerys_Velaryon_and_his_dragon_Vermax_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg/525px-Prince_Jacaerys_Velaryon_and_his_dragon_Vermax_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/9/91/Prince_Jacaerys_Velaryon_and_his_dragon_Vermax_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg/700px-Prince_Jacaerys_Velaryon_and_his_dragon_Vermax_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg 2x\" /></a><div>Vermax and <a href=\"/index.php/Jacaerys_Velaryon\" title=\"Jacaerys Velaryon\">Jacaerys Velaryon</a>, by Jota Saraiva ©</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Owner</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Jacaerys_Velaryon\" title=\"Jacaerys Velaryon\">Jacaerys Velaryon</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Species</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">Dragon</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\nIn&#160;<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_114_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">114</a>–<a href=\"/index.php/120_AC\" title=\"120 AC\">120&#160;AC</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\nIn&#160;5<sup>th</sup> day of the 1<sup>st</sup> moon of <a href=\"/index.php/130_AC\" title=\"130 AC\">130&#160;AC</a>,&#160;the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_in_the_Gullet\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Battle in the Gullet\">Gullet</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rise_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"The Rise of the Dragon\">The Rise of the Dragon</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rogue_Prince\" title=\"The Rogue Prince\">The Rogue Prince</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Princess_and_the_Queen\" title=\"The Princess and the Queen\">The Princess and the Queen</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><span style=\"white-space:nowrap\">TV series</span></th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"House of the Dragon\">House of the Dragon</a></i>: <a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon_-_Season_1\" title=\"House of the Dragon - Season 1\">Season 1</a> | <a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon_-_Season_2\" title=\"House of the Dragon - Season 2\">2</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Vermax</b> was a <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragon</a> ridden by Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Jacaerys_Velaryon\" title=\"Jacaerys Velaryon\">Jacaerys Velaryon</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance_and_Character\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance and Character</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Dragon_Egg\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Dragon Egg</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#The_Dance_of_the_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">The Dance of the Dragons</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Known_dragonriders_of_Vermax\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Known dragonriders of Vermax</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Behind_the_Scenes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Behind the Scenes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Notes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance_and_Character\">Appearance and Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Vermax&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance and Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In <a href=\"/index.php/129_AC\" title=\"129 AC\">129&#160;AC</a>, Vermax was thriving and growing larger every year.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Vermax became ill-tempered when in proximity of snow, ice, and cold.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_a_son_for_a_son.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_a_son_for_a_son.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Despite his youth, Vermax was strong.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Vermax's coloring is not stated in the books. However, he is depicted as green in illustrations from <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rise_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"The Rise of the Dragon\">The Rise of the Dragon</a></i>;<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtrotd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtrotd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> more specifically, in the television adaptation <i><a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"House of the Dragon\">House of the Dragon</a></i>, he has olive green scales and pale orange wing membranes.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> His <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonflame\" title=\"Dragonflame\">flames</a> were possibly orange, too.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Gullet_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Gullet-7\">&#91;N 1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Vermax&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Jacaerys_introduces_Sara_Snow_to_Vermax_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/a/a7/Jacaerys_introduces_Sara_Snow_to_Vermax_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg/350px-Jacaerys_introduces_Sara_Snow_to_Vermax_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"247\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/a/a7/Jacaerys_introduces_Sara_Snow_to_Vermax_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg/525px-Jacaerys_introduces_Sara_Snow_to_Vermax_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/a/a7/Jacaerys_introduces_Sara_Snow_to_Vermax_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg/700px-Jacaerys_introduces_Sara_Snow_to_Vermax_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Jacaerys_introduces_Sara_Snow_to_Vermax_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Jacaerys_Velaryon\" title=\"Jacaerys Velaryon\">Jacaerys Velaryon</a> introduces <a href=\"/index.php/Sara_Snow\" title=\"Sara Snow\">Sara Snow</a> to Vermax, by Jota Saraiva ©</div></div></div>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Dragon_Egg\">Dragon Egg</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Vermax&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Dragon Egg\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a>'s three eldest sons by her husband, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Laenor_Velaryon\" title=\"Laenor Velaryon\">Laenor Velaryon</a>, were <a href=\"/index.php/Jacaerys_Velaryon\" title=\"Jacaerys Velaryon\">Jacaerys</a> (b. <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_114_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">114&#160;AC</a>), <a href=\"/index.php/Lucerys_Velaryon\" title=\"Lucerys Velaryon\">Lucerys</a> (b. <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_115_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">115&#160;AC</a>), and <a href=\"/index.php/Joffrey_Velaryon\" title=\"Joffrey Velaryon\">Joffrey</a> (b. <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_117_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">117&#160;AC</a>). The <a href=\"/index.php/Greens\" title=\"Greens\">rival faction</a> at court, who supported her stepmother <a href=\"/index.php/Alicent_Hightower\" title=\"Alicent Hightower\">Alicent Hightower</a> and her children, spread the accusation that Rhaenyra's three sons were not really Laenor's, but <a href=\"/index.php/Bastard\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bastard\">bastards</a> fathered by Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Harwin_Strong\" title=\"Harwin Strong\">Harwin Strong</a>. Rhaenyra's father, King <a href=\"/index.php/Viserys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Viserys I Targaryen\">Viserys I</a>, in an effort to confirm that he considered Rhaenyra and her sons the true heirs to the throne, decreed that a <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon_egg\" title=\"Dragon egg\">dragon egg</a> would be put in the cradle of each of the boys, to bond with the dragons that hatched from them. Those who doubted the paternity of Rhaenyra's sons also doubted that the eggs would ever hatch, but they were quickly disappointed, as each of the eggs soon hatched in turn. The hatchlings were named Vermax (bonded with Jacaerys), <a href=\"/index.php/Arrax\" title=\"Arrax\">Arrax</a> (bonded with Lucerys), and <a href=\"/index.php/Tyraxes\" title=\"Tyraxes\">Tyraxes</a> (bonded with Joffrey). The exact date each hatched is not known, but the last seems to have hatched by no later than about <a href=\"/index.php/120_AC\" title=\"120 AC\">120&#160;AC</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"The_Dance_of_the_Dragons\">The Dance of the Dragons</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Vermax&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: The Dance of the Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>By the time the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a> began in <a href=\"/index.php/129_AC\" title=\"129 AC\">129&#160;AC</a>, Vermax was big enough to ride. Prince Jacaerys flew <a href=\"/index.php/North\" title=\"North\">north</a> on his back, as a messenger for his mother, Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a>, to treat with <a href=\"/index.php/Jeyne_Arryn\" title=\"Jeyne Arryn\">Jeyne Arryn</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Lady_of_the_Eyrie\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Lady of the Eyrie\">Lady of the Eyrie</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Desmond_Manderly\" title=\"Desmond Manderly\">Desmond Manderly</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_White_Harbor\" title=\"Lord of White Harbor\">Lord of White Harbor</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Cregan_Stark\" title=\"Cregan Stark\">Cregan Stark</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Winterfell\" title=\"Lord of Winterfell\">Lord of Winterfell</a>. The mission was a success, as all three declared for Rhaenyra and her <a href=\"/index.php/Blacks\" title=\"Blacks\">blacks</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_a_son_for_a_son.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_a_son_for_a_son.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Snow, ice, and cold made Vermax irritable, so Jacaerys did not stay in the north for long, despite receiving a warm welcome at <a href=\"/index.php/Winterfell\" title=\"Winterfell\">Winterfell</a>. In his <a href=\"/index.php/The_Testimony_of_Mushroom\" title=\"The Testimony of Mushroom\">testimony</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Mushroom\" title=\"Mushroom\">Mushroom</a> claims that Vermax laid a clutch of <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon_egg\" title=\"Dragon egg\">eggs</a> in the depths of the <a href=\"/index.php/Crypts_of_Winterfell\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Crypts of Winterfell\">crypts of Winterfell</a>, but this tale is most likely false. <a href=\"/index.php/Archmaester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Archmaester\">Archmaester</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Gyldayn\" title=\"Gyldayn\">Gyldayn</a> states it is difficult to tell the sex of a dragon, but that no other source mentions that Vermax ever produced an egg, and dismisses <a href=\"/index.php/Septon\" title=\"Septon\">Septon</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Barth\" title=\"Barth\">Barth</a>'s theory that dragons can change sex as \"ludicrous\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_a_son_for_a_son.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_a_son_for_a_son.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_north:_winterfell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_north:_winterfell.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Prince Jacaerys used Vermax in battle, during the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_in_the_Gullet\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Battle in the Gullet\">Battle in the Gullet</a>. There, Vermax attacked the <a href=\"/index.php/Triarchy\" title=\"Triarchy\">Triarchy</a>'s fleet, and victory seemed at hand. But Vermax flew too low, possibly wounded from a <a href=\"/index.php/Crossbow\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Crossbow\">crossbow</a> bolt to the eye or pulled down by a grapnel, and crashed into a burning <a href=\"/index.php/Galley\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Galley\">galley</a>. Jacaerys leapt free and clung to the smoking wreckage of the ship, but was struck by <a href=\"/index.php/Myrish\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Myrish\">Myrish</a> crossbow quarrels until he sank into the sea, dead.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Known_dragonriders_of_Vermax\">Known dragonriders of Vermax</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Vermax&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Known dragonriders of Vermax\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Jacaerys_Velaryon\" title=\"Jacaerys Velaryon\">Jacaerys Velaryon</a> - first and only rider</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Behind_the_Scenes\">Behind the Scenes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Vermax&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Behind the Scenes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Vermax's name may be a reference to the dragon Vermithrax Pejorative, from the 1981 film <i><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dragonslayer_(1981_film)\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Dragonslayer (1981 film)\">Dragonslayer</a></i>. Martin has cited <i>Dragonslayer</i> as one of his favorite fantasy films, calling Vermithrax \"the best dragon ever put on film\" and the one with \"the coolest dragon name as well\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Vermax&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Gullet-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Gullet_7-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">The fireballs spit by Vermax (a green and orange dragon) as well as <a href=\"/index.php/Seasmoke\" title=\"Seasmoke\">Seasmoke</a> (a silver-grey dragon), <a href=\"/index.php/Sheepstealer\" title=\"Sheepstealer\">Sheepstealer</a> (a muddy brown dragon), <a href=\"/index.php/Silverwing\" title=\"Silverwing\">Silverwing</a> (a silvery dragon) and <a href=\"/index.php/Vermithor\" title=\"Vermithor\">Vermithor</a> (a bronze and tan dragon) during the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Gullet\" title=\"Battle of the Gullet\">battle of the Gullet</a> are described as \"blue and orange, red and gold\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Vermax&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, The Dying of the Dragons - The Red Dragon and the Gold.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, The Dying of the Dragons - The Blacks and the Greens.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_a_son_for_a_son.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_a_son_for_a_son.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">3.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_a_son_for_a_son.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\">3.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_a_son_for_a_son.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\">3.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fir